        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 7:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 719 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Rutherfordton, or near Lake Lure, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shingle Hollow, Green Hill, Lake Lure, Chimney Rock State Park,
Chimney Rock Village, Union Mills, Thermal City, and Rutherfordton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
western North Carolina.</instruction>
